---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about Jacky Huynh and his journey back into mechanical engineering."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>

    <h1>
      Mechanical Engineer with a Background in Business Operations
    </h1>

    <p class="intro">
      I'm a Mechanical Engineering graduate from Temple University with
      experience leading business operations, managing projects, and building
      practical solutions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>From Engineering to Entrepreneurship and Back</h2>

    <p>
      I earned my Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering from Temple
      University, where I developed a strong foundation in design, CAD
      modeling, simulation, and collaborative problem-solving.
    </p>

    <p>
      During my time at Temple, I worked on projects involving autonomous
      systems, product design, and prototyping. These experiences reinforced my
      passion for solving complex problems and turning ideas into practical
      solutions.
    </p>

    <p>
      After graduation, I pursued an opportunity to co-found and operate a
      business. Over several years, I led day-to-day operations, managed
      projects, coordinated vendors, and developed systems to support growth.
    </p>

    <p>
      While the experience expanded my perspective and strengthened my
      leadership skills, my long-term goal has always been to build a career in
      engineering.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Leadership Beyond the Classroom</h2>

    <p>
      Running a business provided hands-on experience that complements my
      engineering background.
    </p>

    <p>
      I learned how to manage competing priorities, communicate with diverse
      stakeholders, improve processes, and make decisions with limited
      information.
    </p>

    <p>
      These experiences taught me to think beyond technical solutions and
      consider the people, timelines, budgets, and operational challenges that
      influence successful projects.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Current Focus</h2>

    <p>
      I'm seeking opportunities in mechanical engineering where I can
      contribute to design, product development, manufacturing, or project
      execution while continuing to grow technically and professionally.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="facts">
    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Education</h3>
      <p>B.S. Mechanical Engineering</p>
      <p>Temple University</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Location</h3>
      <p>Greater Philadelphia Area</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-card">
      <h3>Interests</h3>
      <p>CAD • Product Design • Simulation • Process Improvement</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 42rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .facts {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 5rem;
  }

  .fact-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .fact-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .fact-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .facts {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>